  "title": "Senior/ Staff Nurse (Palliative/ Homecare)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Patient Care Support:</strong><br>\nAssist the nursing team in delivering personalized and cost-effective care. Monitor and report patient progress to senior nurses.</li>\n  <li><strong>Patient Discharge &amp; Follow-Up:</strong><br>\nHelp with discharge planning and post-discharge care coordination. Follow up through phone reviews, home visits, and ensure community services are in place.</li>\n  <li><strong>Education &amp; Self-Care:</strong><br>\nEducate patients and families on health conditions and self-care management. Provide guidance on holistic care as needed.</li>\n  <li><strong>Nursing Assessments &amp; Services:</strong><br>\nConduct nursing assessments, create care plans, and provide necessary services (e.g., wound care, medication management, dressing changes).</li>\n  <li><strong>Home Visit Safety &amp; Documentation:</strong><br>\nEnsure safety and infection control during home visits. Document all assessments and services provided.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p><br></p>",
